# Worker task: deploy the patched capture clients fleet-wide

You are a worker on [Typesense Reboot Recovery](../projects/typesense-reboot-recovery/typesense-reboot-recovery-brief.svx). Your step: [Deploy the Patched Capture Clients Fleet-Wide](../projects/typesense-reboot-recovery/deploy-capture-clients-fleet-wide.svx) — read it and the closed patch step for what "patched" means. Load `tailnet-topology` before any ssh; verify hosts with `tailscale status`. Machine notes: blaine is Joel's laptop (hostname reports `Dark-Tower`, may be offline — handle gracefully); panda is decommissioning but may still run capture; use tailnet IPs when MagicDNS fails.

## Hard containment rules

- Discover the real machine set from Run metadata (`machine_id` values in `~/.joelclaw/runs-dev` metadata files — read-only) before assuming.
- On remote machines: `git pull` (or `jj git fetch` + update) in the joelclaw checkout and rebuild/install only capture-client artifacts. Nothing else. No repo resets, no force operations, no service restarts beyond what capture clients need.
- If a machine is unreachable, record it as a gap with the exact command Joel or a session on that machine should run — never claim deployment you didn't verify.
- Do not commit (on any machine).

## The work

The three done-conditions in your step file. Proof standard: condition 2 requires fresh captures FROM EACH updated machine arriving at flagg with the provenance fields — trigger a small pi/claude session remotely (or ask the machine's running session via a note in your Result if that's not possible) and verify the arriving metadata in `~/.joelclaw/runs-dev` or `sessions.db`.

## Deliverables

Step `## Result` filled with the machine table (host, reachable, pulled-to commit, provenance proof or gap), status closed with `closed_at` ONLY if every reachable machine is proven, one brief ledger line. Work autonomously. Do not commit. Print a DONE summary.
